      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You should argue that these policies were designed to maintain neighborhood stability and property values, which were seen as crucial for economic predictability in the mid-20th century. Proponents at the time believed that restricting certain groups to specific areas prevented social unrest and maintained a desirable, orderly environment for investment. Furthermore, zoning was framed as a necessary tool to separate incompatible land uses, ensuring that residential areas remained safe and conducive to stable family life, which was the prevailing economic ideal.",
